WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.360
Today, we are going to talk about a very interesting topic.

2
00:00:03.360 --> 00:00:06.200
We are not only going to talk about how to use AI,

3
00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:12.560
but we are going to take a closer look at how to build a really meaningful cooperation relationship with AI.

4
00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:15.600
So I want to ask you a very key question.

5
00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:18.720
AI, we all know that it is a super powerful tool.

6
00:00:18.720 --> 00:00:22.160
But are you really free to use it?

7
00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:27.520
This question will actually directly affect the way and result of your interaction with these powerful systems.

8
00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:35.520
You see, the difference between simply using AI and actually cooperating with AI is actually a lot.

9
00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:36.400
How do you say it?

10
00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:40.160
You see, using AI on the left may just be to give instructions,

11
00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:42.240
do some automated simple work.

12
00:00:42.240 --> 00:00:44.160
But the cooperation on the right?

13
00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:45.960
This is a kind of partner relationship.

14
00:00:45.960 --> 00:00:47.200
It's a conversation.

15
00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:50.400
It's about getting things done together.

16
00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:53.360
That's the point we're really going to talk about today.

17
00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:54.440
Okay, here's the question.

18
00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:59.120
How do we become a real helper from a user?

19
00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:04.120
Well, actually, we can start with a very simple but very powerful framework.

20
00:01:04.120 --> 00:01:08.480
The core of this framework is the ability you need to have these four things.

21
00:01:08.480 --> 00:01:10.680
That's right, it's this 4D framework.

22
00:01:10.680 --> 00:01:14.320
You see, it contains the first, command, delegation.

23
00:01:14.320 --> 00:01:17.760
That is, you have to figure out what work should be done for AI.

24
00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:19.920
Second, description, description.

25
00:01:19.920 --> 00:01:21.800
How do you talk to it?

26
00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:23.840
Third, judgment, discernment.

27
00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:26.160
What AI gives you, is it good or not?

28
00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:49.940
Finally, fourth,

29
00:01:49.940 --> 00:01:53.740
The key is that your own professional knowledge and judgment

30
00:01:53.740 --> 00:01:57.460
is the basis for AI to play the greatest value.

31
00:01:57.460 --> 00:02:01.700
The best result is definitely not to leave the job to AI and it's fine.

32
00:02:01.700 --> 00:02:04.420
It's you and AI each play their strengths,

33
00:02:04.420 --> 00:02:07.140
come and go, and work together.

34
00:02:07.140 --> 00:02:09.420
Okay, the second is description.

35
00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:12.300
This part is about how you communicate with AI,

36
00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:14.220
tell it what you need.

37
00:02:14.220 --> 00:02:16.100
I think this is really interesting.

38
00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:18.100
He said the most effective communication

39
00:02:18.140 --> 00:02:21.900
Sometimes it's not that kind of super complicated, super long command,

40
00:02:21.900 --> 00:02:24.900
but a deep conversation.

41
00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:26.660
You give it background information in the conversation,

42
00:02:26.660 --> 00:02:28.260
give it an example, give it feedback,

43
00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:31.940
slowly make it into the partner you want.

44
00:02:31.940 --> 00:02:35.180
Okay, after the production of AI,

45
00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:39.020
this brings us to our third D, judgment.

46
00:02:39.020 --> 00:02:42.220
That is, you have to be able to criticize the bottom,

47
00:02:42.220 --> 00:02:44.820
evaluate the content of AI production.

48
00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:47.540
I have to emphasize that this is really very,

49
00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:48.820
very important.

50
00:02:48.820 --> 00:02:51.900
This is a responsibility that can never be compromised.

51
00:02:51.900 --> 00:02:54.940
You have to be the ultimate quality judge

52
00:02:54.940 --> 00:02:57.100
of all AI production content.

53
00:02:57.100 --> 00:02:58.900
You have to use your professional judgment

54
00:02:58.900 --> 00:03:02.060
to make up for the blind spots or limitations that AI may have.

55
00:03:02.060 --> 00:03:03.980
Okay, the last D,

56
00:03:03.980 --> 00:03:08.060
but also very important, is judgment.

57
00:03:08.060 --> 00:03:11.060
The meaning is that we have to use AI

58
00:03:11.060 --> 00:03:14.780
in a responsible and moral way.

59
00:03:14.780 --> 00:03:17.740
You have to remember that no matter how much AI has done for you,

60
00:03:17.740 --> 00:03:20.660
the most important person responsible for this result is you.

61
00:03:20.660 --> 00:03:23.340
And the impact this job may have on others,

62
00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:26.180
this responsibility is still on you.

63
00:03:26.180 --> 00:03:28.220
Of course, it's not a matter of one or two days

64
00:03:28.220 --> 00:03:30.300
to master these abilities.

65
00:03:30.300 --> 00:03:31.980
It's more like a journey.

66
00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:35.340
The point is to practice, not to pursue perfection.

67
00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:37.460
So how do you train this ability?

68
00:03:37.460 --> 00:03:38.860
It's actually very natural.

69
00:03:38.860 --> 00:03:40.100
Your AI upbringing

70
00:03:40.100 --> 00:03:43.660
is built up in this continuous cycle.

71
00:03:43.700 --> 00:03:45.340
You first assign tasks,

72
00:03:45.340 --> 00:03:47.260
then describe your needs,

73
00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:49.500
then judge the good and bad,

74
00:03:49.500 --> 00:03:51.260
and at the same time keep it safe.

75
00:03:51.260 --> 00:03:54.140
Then, you repeat it over and over again.

76
00:03:54.140 --> 00:03:57.180
Again and again, you will get better and better.

77
00:03:57.180 --> 00:03:59.260
So you see, the ultimate goal

78
00:03:59.260 --> 00:04:03.500
is really not to make you 100% perfect,

79
00:04:03.500 --> 00:04:06.420
but to cultivate a kind of awareness,

80
00:04:06.420 --> 00:04:07.940
through thinking,

81
00:04:07.940 --> 00:04:10.500
and working with AI.

82
00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:12.340
So after talking so much,

83
00:04:12.340 --> 00:04:16.740
what does all this mean to you and your future job?

84
00:04:16.740 --> 00:04:19.540
Well, I think this is both your responsibility

85
00:04:19.540 --> 00:04:21.700
and also a great opportunity for you.

86
00:04:21.700 --> 00:04:23.460
Why is it an opportunity?

87
00:04:23.460 --> 00:04:26.060
Because when you start to apply this framework,

88
00:04:26.060 --> 00:04:29.620
you can turn AI from a machine that only listens to instructions

89
00:04:29.620 --> 00:04:32.260
into a real thinking partner.

90
00:04:32.260 --> 00:04:33.660
And the key to this transformation

91
00:04:33.660 --> 00:04:35.780
comes from the kind of

92
00:04:35.780 --> 00:04:38.620
in-depth conversation we talked about earlier.

93
00:04:38.620 --> 00:04:40.500
I think this sentence is

94
00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:43.260
the essence of all the content today.

95
00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:46.420
The AI system itself is very powerful,

96
00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:49.820
but how useful and safe they can be

97
00:04:49.820 --> 00:04:52.660
depends entirely on us.

98
00:04:52.660 --> 00:04:56.220
The future is a cooperation between you and AI.

99
00:04:56.220 --> 00:04:58.180
Now you have a way,

100
00:04:58.180 --> 00:05:00.620
the only problem left is

101
00:05:00.620 --> 00:05:04.220
what kind of future do you want to create together?
